                  <summary>Fragment of an untitled treatise on ethics and etiquette by an unnamed author.</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068451 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068452" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1577x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Fragment of an untitled treatise on ethics and etiquette by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at the beginning, having lost at least fifty-six folios according to Persian foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 159r): completed Thursday, 17 Jumādá al-Ūlá 940/14 December 1533. 
</p>
                        <p>Mannered naskh combining early nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Foliated in Persian. 
</p>
                        <p>First and last folios cut and remounted in new margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Binding damaged, with only the front board, detached, still extant. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition fair. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author/>
                  </msItem>
